to the bank right now.

506
00:31:32.182 --> 00:31:35.143
Tell them to hurry their asses. I wanna
put some eyes in that bank as well.

507
00:31:35.185 --> 00:31:37.938
- Was the crime scene bad?
- Yes. very bad.

508
00:31:38.021 --> 00:31:41.525
We think that she set up the robbery
at the Super Center. and then it went bad.

509
00:31:41.608 --> 00:31:42.984
She left in a getaway car.

510
00:31:43.068 --> 00:31:44.068
Or…

511
00:31:46.279 --> 00:31:47.155
Talk.

512
00:31:47.239 --> 00:31:48.281
In the video.

513
00:31:48.365 --> 00:31:51.535
she looks as though
she was a victim caught up in a robbery.

514
00:31:52.327 --> 00:31:54.538
Okay. so how do you
explain her killing her boss?

515
00:31:54.621 --> 00:31:56.415
She was evicted from her home today.

516
00:31:56.498 --> 00:31:58.579
Which is all the more reason
for her to rob the bank.

517
00:31:58.625 --> 00:32:01.169
Or maybe it was just too much for her.
and she wanted her pay.

518
00:32:01.753 --> 00:32:04.548
She got caught up in a robbery
and snapped. so she killed him.

519
00:32:08.593 --> 00:32:09.593
You. come with me.

520
00:32:15.725 --> 00:32:19.187
20s. please. I need some... I need 20s.

521
00:32:20.981 --> 00:32:22.524
No!

522
00:32:28.363 --> 00:32:31.616
Shots fired. sir! Get down!
We have shots fired!

523
00:32:36.955 --> 00:32:39.749
Hands up! Hands up now!

524
00:32:39.833 --> 00:32:42.586
- All right! It ain't even us!
- Keep your hands up!

525
00:32:42.669 --> 00:32:46.006
Look. the lady's still robbing the bank.
All right. This is the security guard.

526
00:32:46.089 --> 00:32:47.089
Did she shoot at you?

527
00:32:47.132 --> 00:32:50.177
Nah. When I tried to take her down.
her gun went off.

528
00:32:50.260 --> 00:32:52.220
This motherfucker wasn't doing shit.

529
00:32:52.721 --> 00:32:54.514
Well. that was stupid.

530
00:32:56.224 --> 00:32:57.476
Get up!

531
00:32:57.559 --> 00:32:58.602
Get up!

532
00:33:00.020 --> 00:33:01.229
Get up!

533
00:33:01.313 --> 00:33:04.691
Stop acting like that!
I didn't do nothing to you!

534
00:33:04.774 --> 00:33:05.984
Tessa!

535
00:33:06.067 --> 00:33:09.946
You gave me that money. You set me up!

536
00:33:10.030 --> 00:33:14.159
I just needed to get the $40
and take it to the school.

537
00:33:14.242 --> 00:33:16.661
<i>On the scene now
at Benevolent Bank and Trust</i>

538
00:33:16.745 --> 00:33:19.122
<i>where there is a robbery in progress.</i>

539
00:33:19.206 --> 00:33:22.417
<i>The police received a silent alarm.
and when they got on the scene.</i>

540
00:33:22.501 --> 00:33:23.877
<i>they heard a gunshot.</i>

541
00:33:23.960 --> 00:33:26.755
<i>And. Martha. we heard it as well
just moments ago.</i>

542
00:33:26.838 --> 00:33:27.839
<i>It was chaos.</i>

543
00:33:27.923 --> 00:33:30.008
Two gentlemen came running out of the door

544
00:33:30.091 --> 00:33:32.802
and were immediately met
with commands from the police.

545
00:33:32.886 --> 00:33:34.429
<i>Now. from what we have learned.</i>

546
00:33:34.513 --> 00:33:37.724
<i>the suspect's name is
Janiyah Ann Wiltkinson.</i>

547
00:33:37.807 --> 00:33:41.228
<i>Our sources at the police department
have shared that she is wanted in question</i>

548
00:33:41.311 --> 00:33:42.854
<i>for an earlier murder</i>

549
00:33:42.938 --> 00:33:46.858
<i>that happened at the Super Center
on Beneville Boulevard near the branch.</i>

550
00:34:00.080 --> 00:34:01.665
Tessa. give me the phone.

551
00:34:08.797 --> 00:34:10.423
Benevolent Bank and Trust.

552
00:34:12.384 --> 00:34:13.426
Uh. yes.

553
00:34:17.722 --> 00:34:18.974
It's for you.

554
00:34:24.145 --> 00:34:25.480
Who's calling me?

555
00:34:26.189 --> 00:34:29.150
Uh. our bank lines run on cell phones

556
00:34:29.234 --> 00:34:31.027
so we can move around.

557
00:34:41.162 --> 00:34:42.247
Hello?

558
00:34:42.330 --> 00:34:44.499
- <i>Janiyah. this is Chief Wilson...</i>
- Mnh-mnh.

559
00:34:44.583 --> 00:34:45.959
- Okay.
- Mnh-mnh.

560
00:34:46.960 --> 00:34:49.462
Get back. please!

561
00:34:54.050 --> 00:34:55.594
Mobile unit is here.

562
00:34:55.677 --> 00:34:57.512
She hung up. Call her back.

563
00:34:57.596 --> 00:35:00.223
- Where in the hell is the negotiator?
- He's close. sir.

564
00:35:00.307 --> 00:35:01.307
Sir.

565
00:35:01.725 --> 00:35:02.642
What is it?

566
00:35:02.726 --> 00:35:04.436
Perhaps I have a better shot.

567
00:35:04.519 --> 00:35:06.062
And why do you think that?

568
00:35:06.146 --> 00:35:08.481
Female voice. someone she can relate to.

569
00:35:08.565 --> 00:35:09.608
Okay.

570
00:35:10.191 --> 00:35:12.527
And what makes you think
that's the right thing to do?

571
00:35:13.111 --> 00:35:15.947
I mean. she was robbed by a man.
She was set up by a man.

572
00:35:16.031 --> 00:35:17.032
She killed a man.

573
00:35:19.618 --> 00:35:21.661
And how are you so sure she was set up?

574
00:35:21.745 --> 00:35:22.912
I just feel it. sir.

575
00:35:24.706 --> 00:35:26.207
- Come with me.
- Yes. sir.

576
00:35:27.042 --> 00:35:29.544
- If anything goes wrong. it's your ass.
- Yes. sir.

577
00:35:35.008 --> 00:35:36.468
She doesn't wanna talk to you.

578
00:35:39.346 --> 00:35:40.680
Can you put me on speaker?

579
00:35:43.892 --> 00:35:44.892
You're on.

580
00:35:45.852 --> 00:35:47.062
Hi. Janiyah.

581
00:35:47.145 --> 00:35:48.855
<i>My name is Detective Raymond.</i>

582
00:35:52.442 --> 00:35:54.736
Why are all the police
out there like that?

583
00:35:55.987 --> 00:35:56.905
Negotiator's here.

584
00:35:56.988 --> 00:35:59.240
Great news.
One of my officers made contact.

585
00:35:59.324 --> 00:36:00.825
- Wanna take over?
- Hold on.

586
00:36:01.409 --> 00:36:02.911
- Just let me listen.
- All right.

587
00:36:04.788 --> 00:36:06.389
We got a call the bank was being robbed.

588
00:36:06.456 --> 00:36:07.791
- Oh. no!
<i>- Listen.</i>

589
00:36:07.874 --> 00:36:10.126
I know it may be scary.

590
00:36:10.210 --> 00:36:13.922
but I need to ask.
is everyone in there okay?

591
00:36:14.005 --> 00:36:15.632
We heard a gunshot from inside the bank.

592
00:36:15.715 --> 00:36:17.342
<i>No! No!</i>

593
00:36:17.425 --> 00:36:20.595
It went off when he ran into me.

594
00:36:20.679 --> 00:36:22.681
And then... And then the gun went off!

595
00:36:23.181 --> 00:36:24.683
<i>I hear that. I hear that.</i>

596
00:36:25.558 --> 00:36:27.560
But we have to be very. very careful.

597
00:36:27.644 --> 00:36:31.648
There's a lot of people in there that can
get hurt. and we don't want that. okay?

598
00:36:32.315 --> 00:36:35.652
Listen. I didn't rob the bank.

599
00:36:35.735 --> 00:36:37.946
I just came to cash my check.

600
00:36:38.029 --> 00:36:39.322
<i>That's all.</i>

601
00:36:39.989 --> 00:36:42.575
It's good to know
that you're not robbing the bank.

602
00:36:42.659 --> 00:36:44.494
How about you put the gun down.

603
00:36:44.577 --> 00:36:47.539
just step outside with the backpack
and let's figure this out?

604
00:36:47.622 --> 00:36:51.000
She gave me the money. and I told her
I didn't want all of that money!

605
00:36:51.084 --> 00:36:53.795
Did you call the police?
Why would you do that?

606
00:36:53.878 --> 00:36:56.798
Why did you do that?

607
00:36:56.881 --> 00:36:59.592
Stop screaming!

608
00:36:59.676 --> 00:37:01.553
<i>Janiyah. listen to me.</i>

609
00:37:01.636 --> 00:37:04.013
This seems to be one big misunderstanding.

610
00:37:04.097 --> 00:37:08.560
It is. because I didn't come here
to rob the bank!

611
00:37:09.477 --> 00:37:11.187
That's what I'm trying to tell you!

612
00:37:11.271 --> 00:37:12.605
I come here all the time.

613
00:37:12.689 --> 00:37:14.357
Why would you do that?

614
00:37:14.441 --> 00:37:15.734
Janiyah. it's okay.

615
00:37:15.817 --> 00:37:19.696
Okay. well. you never came into the bank
with a backpack and a gun.

616
00:37:19.779 --> 00:37:21.698
Can you see how this can all be confusing?

617
00:37:21.781 --> 00:37:22.781
She's doing good.

618
00:37:22.824 --> 00:37:23.742
Good.

619
00:37:23.825 --> 00:37:27.245
This gun is not even mine!

620
00:37:28.246 --> 00:37:30.707
Okay. well. let's just put it down

621
00:37:31.291 --> 00:37:34.502
and come outside and let's talk about it.
Let's get it all sorted out.

622
00:37:34.586 --> 00:37:35.837
<i>No. no. no.</i>

623
00:37:35.920 --> 00:37:37.964
No. all I need is my money.

624
00:37:38.047 --> 00:37:40.383
because I have to get
the $40 to the school.

625
00:37:40.467 --> 00:37:42.927
because she gotta eat.

626
00:37:43.011 --> 00:37:45.096
And if she doesn't eat.
they're gonna tease her!

627
00:37:45.180 --> 00:37:47.474
I just… I… I…

628
00:37:49.392 --> 00:37:51.853
I just came to get the money for my baby!

629
00:37:51.936 --> 00:37:54.147
<i>Okay. okay. and I can do that.</i>

630
00:37:54.230 --> 00:37:56.274
<i>I just need you to come out
and talk to me first.</i>

631
00:37:56.858 --> 00:37:58.067
You're lying.

632
00:37:58.777 --> 00:38:00.403
You can't help me.

633
00:38:00.487 --> 00:38:02.572
Nobody ever helps me!

634
00:38:02.655 --> 00:38:04.157
I do it all myself.

635
00:38:04.240 --> 00:38:07.619
Every fucking thing. I do it myself!

636
00:38:08.703 --> 00:38:11.080
You wanna... You wanna kill me!

637
00:38:11.164 --> 00:38:14.083
You wanna blame me
for robbing this bank. and I didn't do it.

638
00:38:15.168 --> 00:38:19.088
And you wanna lock me up.
and then what about my baby?

639
00:38:19.172 --> 00:38:20.882
What about my baby?

640
00:38:22.175 --> 00:38:23.301
<i>You're lying!</i>

641
00:38:23.384 --> 00:38:25.762
Okay. well. the best way we can do that

642
00:38:25.845 --> 00:38:28.598
is by helping you
get your side of the truth out.

643
00:38:32.268 --> 00:38:35.146
How many people
are in there with you. Janiyah?

644
00:38:35.897 --> 00:38:39.234
I don't know. I don't know. Uh…

645
00:38:44.030 --> 00:38:46.825
If you don't wanna come out right now.
can you at least let them out?

646
00:38:46.908 --> 00:38:49.202
No one else needs to get hurt. Janiyah.

647
00:38:49.285 --> 00:38:50.912
I don't want anybody to get hurt!

648
00:38:50.995 --> 00:38:53.596
That's what I'm trying to tell you.
I didn't come here to do that!

649
00:38:56.626 --> 00:38:58.837
Hang up the phone. Hang it up!

650
00:38:58.920 --> 00:39:02.006
She hung up.

651
00:39:02.715 --> 00:39:04.801
Hey! Is there an electrical issue?

652
00:39:04.884 --> 00:39:07.303
Why are the lights strobing?
Is that why we lost her?

653
00:39:07.387 --> 00:39:09.180
Get her back on the phone right now!

654
00:39:09.681 --> 00:39:11.349
Dan. do you wanna take over now?

655
00:39:11.432 --> 00:39:15.562
- No. no. she actually did really well.
- All right. Good.

656
00:39:15.645 --> 00:39:17.814
And she's established trust
with Detective Raymond.

657
00:39:17.897 --> 00:39:19.983
- Mm-hmm.
- I think she should stay.

658
00:39:21.568 --> 00:39:22.694
Where'd you learn this?

659
00:39:22.777 --> 00:39:25.280
I was a negotiation specialist
in the army.

660
00:39:25.989 --> 00:39:26.823
Hoorah.

661
00:39:26.906 --> 00:39:27.906
Mm-hmm.

662
00:39:29.409 --> 00:39:30.994
Ah.

663
00:39:31.661 --> 00:39:35.582
Here... Here's your money. Miss Wiltkinson.

664
00:39:36.207 --> 00:39:37.207
Janiyah.

665
00:39:39.794 --> 00:39:40.794
Janiyah.

666
00:39:41.379 --> 00:39:42.463
There... There's your money.

667
00:39:45.425 --> 00:39:46.425
You know…

668
00:39:48.219 --> 00:39:52.390
I think this has all been
a misunderstanding.

669
00:39:55.435 --> 00:39:56.936
But we can fix it.

670
00:39:57.896 --> 00:40:02.859
I... I can tell them this is all a mistake.

671
00:40:04.277 --> 00:40:05.737
Would you like us to do that?

672
00:40:09.198 --> 00:40:10.575
Can you give this to my daughter?

673
00:40:14.329 --> 00:40:16.205
- Take it!
- I... I...

674
00:40:16.289 --> 00:40:17.332
Please.

675
00:40:20.668 --> 00:40:23.755
I'm sure she would want you
to give this to her yourself.

676
00:40:27.008 --> 00:40:28.384
He ain't gonna let me.

677
00:40:36.476 --> 00:40:38.937
- Tell them to close the blinds.
- Um…

678
00:40:39.020 --> 00:40:40.146
Now!

679
00:40:40.229 --> 00:40:43.650
Tessa. Rayah. close the blinds. It's okay.

680
00:40:45.944 --> 00:40:47.070
Hurry. run!

681
00:40:47.570 --> 00:40:49.364
It's okay. It's okay. Just do it.

682
00:40:52.659 --> 00:40:54.786
All the way! Pull it all the way down!

683
00:40:58.247 --> 00:41:00.208
- And come back over here. Hurry.
- Come on.

684
00:41:01.209 --> 00:41:04.295
Okay. Okay.

685
00:41:09.300 --> 00:41:10.551
Surveillance is up.

686
00:41:10.635 --> 00:41:13.137
- All right. let's zoom in.
- Zoom in!

687
00:41:16.933 --> 00:41:19.310
- Where in the hell's the bomb squad?
- Moving into position.

688
00:41:19.394 --> 00:41:22.772
All right. get someone in here
to tell me what that is right there.

689
00:41:22.855 --> 00:41:24.065
Copy that.

690
00:41:57.390 --> 00:41:59.100
I need to sit down.

691
00:42:01.644 --> 00:42:03.688
Uh. oh yeah.

692
00:42:03.771 --> 00:42:05.064
Um…

693
00:42:05.898 --> 00:42:07.567
Go get her a chair.

694
00:42:07.650 --> 00:42:08.901
Go!

695
00:42:12.989 --> 00:42:15.992
Look. I'm... I'm sorry. okay?

696
00:42:16.075 --> 00:42:18.327
I know you all got lives to get back to.

697
00:42:18.411 --> 00:42:20.079
Then let us go!

698
00:42:20.163 --> 00:42:21.289
I'm sorry!

699
00:42:21.372 --> 00:42:22.498
I…

700
00:42:24.000 --> 00:42:27.462
I just need a minute to figure this out.

701
00:42:27.545 --> 00:42:30.256
Young lady. ain't nothing to figure out.

702
00:42:30.339 --> 00:42:32.341
Just give yourself up.

703
00:42:33.509 --> 00:42:35.344
I can't let him kill me.

704
00:42:48.816 --> 00:42:51.027
I don't know what's the matter with y'all.

705
00:42:51.652 --> 00:42:53.654
We ain't never stolen nothing from nobody.

706
00:42:53.738 --> 00:42:55.239
I haven't either.

707
00:42:55.323 --> 00:42:56.616
Then what is all this?

708
00:42:56.699 --> 00:42:58.868
Okay. can we... Can we not?

709
00:42:58.951 --> 00:43:01.370
She said she wasn't trying
to rob the bank.

710
00:43:01.454 --> 00:43:02.830
Let's not upset her.

711
00:43:02.914 --> 00:43:04.791
Shit. this is upsetting!

712
00:43:04.874 --> 00:43:08.461
Y'all don't wanna work
for nothing no more.

713
00:43:08.544 --> 00:43:09.712
I am a veteran!

714
00:43:09.796 --> 00:43:12.965
We fought long and hard
for y'all to have all these freedoms

715
00:43:13.049 --> 00:43:14.926
and look at the thanks we get.

716
00:43:15.760 --> 00:43:16.969
Um…

717
00:43:17.053 --> 00:43:19.138
I'm not dealing with this shit.

718
00:43:19.222 --> 00:43:20.807
I'm leaving. Come on.

719
00:43:21.891 --> 00:43:23.851
Is she just gonna let them both walk out?

720
00:43:27.021 --> 00:43:29.357
Hey. we got two hostages coming out.

721
00:43:30.650 --> 00:43:32.985
Just a little further. okay? All right?

722
00:43:33.569 --> 00:43:35.947
Lock the door! Lock the door.

723
00:43:40.785 --> 00:43:43.162
All right! Come back.
Come back. Come back.

724
00:44:01.931 --> 00:44:04.350
Janiyah. you don't have to do this!

725
00:44:04.433 --> 00:44:07.019
We can all walk out of here together!

726
00:44:12.316 --> 00:44:14.527
I can't let him kill me.

727
00:44:17.280 --> 00:44:19.157
Who's gonna take care of my daughter?

728
00:44:20.867 --> 00:44:22.869
She's all I have.

729
00:44:26.998 --> 00:44:27.998
I just…

730
00:44:30.084 --> 00:44:33.045
I need you to stay with me. okay? Please.

731
00:44:33.129 --> 00:44:35.965
I don't ask nobody for nothing. Please.

732
00:44:36.048 --> 00:44:37.550
Okay? I just…

733
00:44:38.801 --> 00:44:41.637
I just need to work this out. okay?

734
00:45:01.115 --> 00:45:03.618
Just gotta work this out.

735
00:45:06.871 --> 00:45:08.206
Just need to think.

736
00:45:15.922 --> 00:45:18.299
She's gonna kill me. She's mad at me.

737
00:45:19.300 --> 00:45:21.928
Tessa. you need to stay calm.

738
00:45:22.011 --> 00:45:23.888
She's not gonna hurt you.

739
00:45:23.971 --> 00:45:26.515
Why can't we just run for the door?
She let them go.

740
00:45:30.978 --> 00:45:33.564
This lady is elderly. She can't run.

741
00:45:33.648 --> 00:45:36.150
Can't I go with Rayah? Please!

742
00:45:36.234 --> 00:45:37.526
We gotta do something.

743
00:45:37.610 --> 00:45:39.320
- Don't.
- I can't take it.

744
00:45:40.446 --> 00:45:44.408
She has a bomb in her backpack.

745
00:45:44.492 --> 00:45:46.994
Oh my God.

746
00:45:48.829 --> 00:45:49.914
A bomb?

747
00:45:51.165 --> 00:45:54.710
All these years. Oh God.
I don't wanna leave out like that.

748
00:45:58.339 --> 00:46:00.633
Here you go. Yeah.

749
00:46:01.968 --> 00:46:04.679
There. There.

750
00:46:07.515 --> 00:46:08.515
Here!

751
00:46:10.726 --> 00:46:13.562
Okay.

752
00:46:15.648 --> 00:46:16.732
All right.

753
00:46:16.816 --> 00:46:18.025
Sit down!

754
00:46:19.068 --> 00:46:20.236
Sit!

755
00:46:28.661 --> 00:46:30.955
Have you heard of a robber
getting chairs for people?

756
00:46:31.038 --> 00:46:33.541
No. but you saw the crime scenes.

757
00:46:38.170 --> 00:46:39.171
Now…

758
00:46:39.922 --> 00:46:42.508
Now you don't have to stand up.

759
00:46:42.591 --> 00:46:46.721
I know what it feels like
to be on your feet all day.

760
00:46:50.808 --> 00:46:53.102
Chief. all right.
we got the blueprints for the bank.

761
00:46:53.185 --> 00:46:56.063
We can go in now. flash grenade. storm it.

762
00:46:56.147 --> 00:46:57.606
Teller said she had a bomb.

763
00:46:57.690 --> 00:46:59.650
I'm not so sure
she has any munitions training.

764
00:46:59.734 --> 00:47:02.153
- Are you sure about that?
- Not that we know of.

765
00:47:02.695 --> 00:47:03.904
It could be fake.

766
00:47:03.988 --> 00:47:07.241
Or she could have learned it
from the internet. and it's real.

767
00:47:07.325 --> 00:47:11.120
Okay. Well. since we don't know right now.
we're just gonna stand down and wait.

768
00:47:11.203 --> 00:47:13.080
We can't get in there with four hostages.

769
00:47:14.040 --> 00:47:14.874
Look.

770
00:47:14.957 --> 00:47:17.084
- I think we should get the FBI in here.
- Shit.

771
00:47:17.168 --> 00:47:19.920
- All right?
- This is not your average bank robber.

772
00:47:20.004 --> 00:47:22.131
No. it's not. She's a murderer.

773
00:47:22.882 --> 00:47:24.884
She didn't even try
to stop them from walking out.

774
00:47:25.384 --> 00:47:27.928
She's literally getting chairs for people.

775
00:47:28.012 --> 00:47:31.265
- Yeah.
- A witness said this is not like her.

776
00:47:31.974 --> 00:47:34.477
Another witness said
that she's a good girl.

777
00:47:34.560 --> 00:47:36.687
I really think she may have just snapped.

778
00:47:36.771 --> 00:47:39.023
Okay. so what's stopping her
from snapping out

779
00:47:39.106 --> 00:47:40.441
and blowing up the damn bank?

780
00:47:40.524 --> 00:47:41.984
Now look. look.

781
00:47:42.068 --> 00:47:44.278
This detective has a good eye. all right?

782
00:47:44.779 --> 00:47:46.655
I think we can end this thing peacefully.

783
00:47:46.739 --> 00:47:50.034
If the FBI gets involved.
they will take over.

784
00:47:50.618 --> 00:47:52.298
They may not have
the same interests as us.

785
00:47:52.787 --> 00:47:54.789
Wait. You mean to stop the robbery. right?

786
00:47:54.872 --> 00:47:56.582
No. I mean to save her life.

787
00:47:58.626 --> 00:48:02.254
We saw her things get thrown out there.
We seen her medicine for her kid.

788
00:48:04.131 --> 00:48:06.258
This is about giving her a chance.

789
00:48:07.718 --> 00:48:08.886
Listen.

790
00:48:08.969 --> 00:48:10.805
Let's hold off
on calling the FBI right now.

791
00:48:10.888 --> 00:48:13.724
Matter of fact.
let's wait for them to call us.

792
00:48:13.808 --> 00:48:15.434
Okay?

793
00:48:17.144 --> 00:48:19.480
Buy some time.
Let's get her back on the phone.

794
00:48:21.607 --> 00:48:22.900
Let's get her back on the line.

795
00:48:22.983 --> 00:48:24.360
- Yes. sir!
- All right.

796
00:48:24.443 --> 00:48:27.405
Dan. do you wanna take over now?

797
00:48:27.488 --> 00:48:29.240
Detective Raymond.

798
00:48:30.491 --> 00:48:31.491
It's on you.

799
00:48:36.330 --> 00:48:38.916
Ooh. these phones!

800
00:48:40.418 --> 00:48:42.670
These phones are driving me crazy.

801
00:48:42.753 --> 00:48:44.547
I wanna unplug 'em.

802
00:48:44.630 --> 00:48:48.717
- How do you unplug the phones?
- It might be better if you talk to them.

803
00:48:48.801 --> 00:48:50.177
Janiyah.

804
00:48:50.261 --> 00:48:52.096
No. I wanna turn 'em off.

805
00:48:52.179 --> 00:48:53.179
Janiyah.

806
00:48:53.222 --> 00:48:54.515
Janiyah.

807
00:48:55.141 --> 00:48:57.226
You might want to answer it.

808
00:48:57.810 --> 00:49:00.896
They may have an idea
on how to get you out safely.

809
00:49:02.356 --> 00:49:03.399
to your daughter.

810
00:49:22.668 --> 00:49:23.668
Hello.

811
00:49:25.045 --> 00:49:27.214
Janiyah. this is Detective Raymond again.

812
00:49:27.298 --> 00:49:30.342
Thanks for answering.
How's it going in there?

813
00:49:32.136 --> 00:49:34.138
Why you got all those police out there?

814
00:49:37.433 --> 00:49:38.767
Just for me?

815
00:49:39.643 --> 00:49:42.188
I told you I wasn't robbing this bank.

816
00:49:42.771 --> 00:49:45.608
We are getting reports
that the suspect has gone live.

817
00:49:45.691 --> 00:49:47.902
and we are getting that feed up
for our viewers.

818
00:49:47.985 --> 00:49:49.403
<i>Yes. yes. we have it.</i>

819
00:49:49.945 --> 00:49:51.822
<i>I just needed to cash my check.</i>

820
00:49:52.656 --> 00:49:55.201
<i>I ain't never stole nothing
a day in my life.</i>

821
00:49:55.910 --> 00:49:58.954
<i>I didn't even know I had this gun.</i>

822
00:49:59.830 --> 00:50:03.209
<i>That is why I'm trying to tell you</i>

823
00:50:03.292 --> 00:50:05.419
<i>I didn't want this to happen.</i>

824
00:50:05.920 --> 00:50:09.673
And you've made that perfectly clear.
so how about we stop this. Janiyah?

825
00:50:10.883 --> 00:50:13.761
I can't come out there
and let them shoot me.

826
00:50:13.844 --> 00:50:15.513
No one is gonna shoot you.

827
00:50:15.596 --> 00:50:16.680
<i>No. he said it.</i>

828
00:50:16.764 --> 00:50:20.351
<i>He said if he sees me again.
he's gonna blow my brains out.</i>

829
00:50:21.560 --> 00:50:22.560
Who said that?

830
00:50:22.978 --> 00:50:24.980
That police officer. he's out there!

831
00:50:25.064 --> 00:50:27.066
He's out there.
He said he was gonna kill me.

832
00:50:27.566 --> 00:50:28.609
<i>The officer out there.</i>

833
00:50:28.692 --> 00:50:30.402
<i>- He ran me off the road earlier.</i>
- Hey!

834
00:50:30.486 --> 00:50:32.905
<i>And that other officer.
she's out there. I saw her.</i>

835
00:50:32.988 --> 00:50:34.949
<i>She had my car towed.</i>

836
00:50:36.534 --> 00:50:40.871
I told them that I needed my car.

837
00:50:40.955 --> 00:50:44.625
<i>because when my daughter gets sick.
I have to take her to the hospital.</i>

838
00:50:44.708 --> 00:50:46.502
I can't wait for an ambulance!

839
00:50:47.920 --> 00:50:49.880
Okay. I got it.

840
00:50:50.548 --> 00:50:52.591
Everything's gonna be okay.

841
00:50:53.092 --> 00:50:55.678
<i>I promise you. no one will hurt you.</i>

842
00:50:55.761 --> 00:50:59.848
Just please come on out
and let's talk about this.

843
00:51:00.432 --> 00:51:02.184
I can't come out there

844
00:51:02.268 --> 00:51:03.811
<i>so they can shoot me.</i>

845
00:51:04.603 --> 00:51:08.232
<i>I needed my money
to get my daughter's medicine.</i>

846
00:51:08.315 --> 00:51:09.358
<i>She's sick.</i>

847
00:51:10.109 --> 00:51:11.485
Janiyah. Janiyah.

848
00:51:12.027 --> 00:51:14.321
Come out and I can help you.

849
00:51:14.947 --> 00:51:17.074
Are you gonna help me with my boss?

850
00:51:17.157 --> 00:51:20.160
<i>He thinks I set up
the robbery at that store.</i>

851
00:51:20.244 --> 00:51:22.079
<i>That man robbed me.</i>

852
00:51:22.162 --> 00:51:23.539
and he hit me.

853
00:51:23.622 --> 00:51:26.125
Just because he read my name tag.

854
00:51:26.208 --> 00:51:29.211
my boss thought he knew me.
and he thought I set it up!

855
00:51:30.671 --> 00:51:34.091
<i>Then he wouldn't give me my check!
He fired me!</i>

856
00:51:34.174 --> 00:51:36.093
<i>My boss fired me.</i>

857
00:51:36.176 --> 00:51:38.220
<i>He fired me because the school called</i>

858
00:51:38.304 --> 00:51:41.265
<i>and told me to come and check on my child.</i>

859
00:51:41.348 --> 00:51:42.683
<i>So he fired me.</i>

860
00:51:43.726 --> 00:51:46.478
My baby's medicine is so expensive.

861
00:51:47.896 --> 00:51:49.481
It's so hard.

862
00:51:49.565 --> 00:51:51.900
<i>I work so hard.</i>

863
00:51:52.401 --> 00:51:53.611
I have two jobs.

864
00:51:53.694 --> 00:51:55.863
I'm barely making it.

865
00:51:57.072 --> 00:51:59.950
I just wanna do what's right for my baby.

866
00:52:00.618 --> 00:52:01.618
That's all.

867
00:52:02.745 --> 00:52:04.163
<i>They took her…</i>

868
00:52:04.246 --> 00:52:07.791
…because she fell in the tub
because she's sick.

869
00:52:07.875 --> 00:52:10.210
She lost her balance. She wanted to…

870
00:52:10.753 --> 00:52:12.588
She wants to bathe herself.

871
00:52:13.172 --> 00:52:14.298
<i>She fell.</i>

872
00:52:14.923 --> 00:52:17.635
<i>She had bruises on her back.
and they blamed me.</i>

873
00:52:19.345 --> 00:52:20.471
<i>They took her.</i>

874
00:52:21.263 --> 00:52:23.390
They didn't care.

875
00:52:28.103 --> 00:52:30.064
Okay. you're right. You're right.

876
00:52:30.147 --> 00:52:33.651
And you have every right
to be upset. okay?

877
00:52:33.734 --> 00:52:36.904
<i>But we can try and figure out
how to get you some help. Janiyah.</i>

878
00:52:37.446 --> 00:52:39.156
I don't want you to get upset.

879
00:52:39.657 --> 00:52:41.950
I got put out.

880
00:52:42.034 --> 00:52:45.120
I got put out today.
We have nowhere to live.

881
00:52:47.247 --> 00:52:49.249
My daughter's medicine…

882
00:52:50.584 --> 00:52:53.295
…was… was put out on the street.

883
00:52:53.962 --> 00:52:56.173
<i>And I told her.</i>

884
00:52:56.256 --> 00:52:58.258
<i>I said. "I just got fired."</i>

885
00:52:58.342 --> 00:53:00.469
<i>"My boss is gonna mail me the check."</i>

886
00:53:00.552 --> 00:53:03.097
<i>She couldn't wait for three days.</i>

887
00:53:03.180 --> 00:53:04.848
Three days!

888
00:53:06.392 --> 00:53:09.353
You don't know how hard it is

889
00:53:09.436 --> 00:53:11.980
to take care of my baby

890
00:53:12.064 --> 00:53:13.565
off of what I make.

891
00:53:15.442 --> 00:53:18.237
I can't get half of what she needs.

892
00:53:19.446 --> 00:53:21.281
And my landlord didn't care.

893
00:53:22.157 --> 00:53:24.451
She just put us out in the rain.

894
00:53:28.455 --> 00:53:30.958
What am I gonna tell her
when she gets home?

895
00:53:33.544 --> 00:53:35.045
It's just too much.

896
00:53:35.129 --> 00:53:37.589
I'm all we got.

897
00:53:41.176 --> 00:53:44.763
Nobody cares. Nobody sees us.

898
00:53:47.099 --> 00:53:48.600
This is my life.

899
00:53:49.101 --> 00:53:53.856
Over and over and over and over.

900
00:53:58.777 --> 00:54:00.738
I just don't know what to do.

901
00:54:02.072 --> 00:54:04.074
You can understand that. right?

902
00:54:05.617 --> 00:54:07.035
I have nothing.

903
00:54:08.120 --> 00:54:09.663
Yes. Yes.

904
00:54:11.206 --> 00:54:13.542
I can see how this can be a lot.

905
00:54:17.463 --> 00:54:18.463
<i>I see you.</i>

906
00:54:20.966 --> 00:54:22.050
I hear you.

907
00:54:24.136 --> 00:54:25.429
Janiyah. I care.

908
00:54:28.724 --> 00:54:30.476
Steady yourself. Okay?

909
00:54:31.101 --> 00:54:33.520
<i>You don't know me. You don't care.</i>

910
00:54:33.604 --> 00:54:37.274
You just want me to come out there
so that man can shoot me.

911
00:54:37.357 --> 00:54:40.819
No. I don't know you.

912
00:54:41.862 --> 00:54:43.363
But I recognize me in you.

913
00:54:44.156 --> 00:54:45.949
Not only was I raised by a single mother.

914
00:54:46.033 --> 00:54:48.452
but I am a single mother. okay?

915
00:54:48.952 --> 00:54:51.371
Everything is on me.

916
00:54:51.872 --> 00:54:54.541
I remember coming home
from school one day. and we were evicted.

917
00:54:54.625 --> 00:54:58.128
My mother was so angry.

918
00:55:00.172 --> 00:55:03.008
<i>She was so upset.</i>

919
00:55:03.091 --> 00:55:05.594
No. go in another direction.

920
00:55:06.094 --> 00:55:08.138
This might trigger her. okay?

921
00:55:08.222 --> 00:55:10.098
<i>How old were you?</i>

922
00:55:12.017 --> 00:55:13.018
I was nine.

923
00:55:14.770 --> 00:55:17.773
My daughter's eight.

924
00:55:19.441 --> 00:55:22.069
So I get it. But you know what?

925
00:55:22.653 --> 00:55:25.489
I remember telling my mother
how much I loved her.

926
00:55:26.990 --> 00:55:28.367
I told her I loved her.

927
00:55:28.450 --> 00:55:30.452
and I told her we would be okay.

928
00:55:32.287 --> 00:55:34.373
<i>And. Janiyah. I promise you.</i>

929
00:55:35.207 --> 00:55:36.542
you will be okay.

930
00:55:38.126 --> 00:55:41.505
You and your baby girl. You will be okay.

931
00:55:45.676 --> 00:55:46.718
You'll be okay.

932
00:55:47.678 --> 00:55:49.513
Chief. we're live.

933
00:55:49.596 --> 00:55:50.597
What?

934
00:55:52.432 --> 00:55:53.517
Okay. put it over here.

935
00:55:58.897 --> 00:56:01.233
Just listen. okay?

936
00:56:01.316 --> 00:56:05.279
It sounds like it's been
a really. really long and trying day.

937
00:56:07.573 --> 00:56:09.992
It sounds like you haven't slept. okay?

938
00:56:10.701 --> 00:56:14.955
I think if you came out.
we could figure this all out. I promise.

939
00:56:15.747 --> 00:56:18.375
Stop saying that!

940
00:56:18.458 --> 00:56:21.962
Stop saying that. I'm not coming out
until you make him leave.

941
00:56:22.045 --> 00:56:24.214
She's getting too emotional
and so are you.

942
00:56:24.298 --> 00:56:26.091
Just get back to asking her to surrender.

943
00:56:26.174 --> 00:56:29.887
The one that ran me off the road and said
he was gonna find a legal way to kill me.

944
00:56:29.970 --> 00:56:33.515
And that other one
who wrote me all those tickets.

945
00:56:33.599 --> 00:56:36.184
- Just listen.
- She knows I can't afford 'em! I told her!

946
00:56:36.268 --> 00:56:39.062
<i>'Cause nobody cares about me.</i>

947
00:56:39.146 --> 00:56:41.565
So. no! I'm not coming out.

948
00:56:45.152 --> 00:56:46.486
What...

949
00:56:48.655 --> 00:56:49.656
What?

950
00:56:54.661 --> 00:56:56.914
I'll check on her.

951
00:57:09.927 --> 00:57:10.927
You okay?

952
00:57:12.054 --> 00:57:13.054
Yeah.

953
00:57:15.682 --> 00:57:16.682
Hey. look.

954
00:57:18.226 --> 00:57:19.728
I know I've been giving you shit.

955
00:57:22.147 --> 00:57:24.232
That was a damn good job in there.

956
00:57:25.484 --> 00:57:26.484
Sorry.

957
00:57:27.527 --> 00:57:29.321
I didn't know all that about you.

958
00:57:33.241 --> 00:57:35.619
- Are we good?
- Yeah.

959
00:57:54.763 --> 00:57:57.015
How in the hell is she on TV?

960
00:57:57.766 --> 00:58:00.978
Chief. one of the hostages
went live on their cell phone. sir.

961
00:58:01.061 --> 00:58:03.021
It was one of the bank tellers.

962
00:58:03.105 --> 00:58:05.691
All right. get the damn
cell signal jammed right now.

963
00:58:05.774 --> 00:58:08.461
I wanna find out who in the hell
is this officer she's talking about.

964
00:58:08.485 --> 00:58:09.319
We're on it. sir.

965
00:58:09.403 --> 00:58:11.923
If she was written a ticket.
I wanna know who wrote that ticket.

966
00:58:11.989 --> 00:58:13.407
Copy that. Jam all cell service…

967
00:58:20.038 --> 00:58:22.916
- Where do these cameras go to?
- Um…

968
00:58:23.000 --> 00:58:25.627
- Uh. to our corporate offices.
- No. no. no.

969
00:58:26.211 --> 00:58:27.963
Where in here? I wanna unplug 'em.

970
00:58:28.463 --> 00:58:32.217
- I don't understand...
- Where are the cameras plugged up in here?

971
00:58:32.300 --> 00:58:33.885
- In the... In the back.
- Take me.

972
00:58:34.553 --> 00:58:37.681
- Don't move.
- Uh…

973
00:58:37.764 --> 00:58:38.932
Don't move.

974
00:58:51.903 --> 00:58:53.155
Did she unlock the door?

975
00:58:53.947 --> 00:58:56.491
- No. she didn't.
- She did. To the left. It's unlocked.

976
00:58:56.575 --> 00:58:58.618
She pushed it hard. It's not.

977
00:59:01.079 --> 00:59:02.497
I gotta get out of here.

978
00:59:02.581 --> 00:59:05.250
I gotta figure out
if that door's unlocked.

979
00:59:05.959 --> 00:59:08.754
Girl. she has a bomb. Sit down.

980
00:59:08.837 --> 00:59:11.006
- I need to get out of here.
- Tessa. Tessa.

981
00:59:11.506 --> 00:59:15.469
- Look. Shh! Keys are behind the counter.
- No! Tessa! Tessa!

982
00:59:24.853 --> 00:59:26.104
Tessa.

983
00:59:27.939 --> 00:59:28.939
Tessa!

984
00:59:45.957 --> 00:59:48.293
You should be careful with that.

985
00:59:48.376 --> 00:59:50.879
Yeah. I know. We worked hard on it.

986
00:59:50.962 --> 00:59:53.131
Do you know a lot about electronics?

987
00:59:53.215 --> 00:59:54.215
No.

988
00:59:54.925 --> 00:59:55.925
Wait.

989
01:00:00.931 --> 01:00:03.767
- What in the hell happened?
- We lost connection. Chief.

990
01:00:06.603 --> 01:00:07.729
Damn it!

991
01:00:12.359 --> 01:00:14.319
Tessa! Tessa. Tessa.

992
01:00:14.945 --> 01:00:16.655
Tessa! Tess...

993
01:00:18.990 --> 01:00:19.991
What are you doing?

994
01:00:21.451 --> 01:00:23.995
Uh. I have to go to the bathroom.

995
01:00:25.539 --> 01:00:27.082
We all have to go.

996
01:00:27.582 --> 01:00:29.835
Okay.

997
01:00:29.918 --> 01:00:32.671
Uh. is there a bathroom in here?

998
01:00:33.255 --> 01:00:34.548
Yes. it's back there.

999
01:00:36.133 --> 01:00:37.425
Okay.

1000
01:00:38.343 --> 01:00:40.220
All right. one at a time.

1001
01:00:52.649 --> 01:00:53.900
No. nothing.

1002
01:00:54.484 --> 01:00:56.069
Not one ticket in her name?

1003
01:00:58.029 --> 01:01:00.407
No. maybe she was in Dale County.
We could check there.

1004
01:01:01.449 --> 01:01:02.449
Okay.

1005
01:01:07.289 --> 01:01:08.665
You're not hearing me!

1006
01:01:10.792 --> 01:01:12.919
What do you think they're doing out there?

1007
01:01:14.462 --> 01:01:15.797
You want a peppermint?

1008
01:01:18.508 --> 01:01:20.760
Is that where all the peppermints go
when I put them out?

1009
01:01:21.803 --> 01:01:25.140
As much as y'all charge for fees.
I know I can have a peppermint.

1010
01:01:25.223 --> 01:01:26.558
Look. I'm sorry.

1011
01:01:26.641 --> 01:01:30.645
but she is holding us all here.
and y'all are treating her like a martyr.

1012
01:01:31.438 --> 01:01:32.856
This is wrong.

1013
01:01:32.939 --> 01:01:34.566
Tessa. enough.

1014
01:01:34.649 --> 01:01:35.734
No. let her talk.

1015
01:01:35.817 --> 01:01:37.444
No. she needs to shut up.

1016
01:01:37.986 --> 01:01:39.279
How old are you?

1017
01:01:39.362 --> 01:01:40.447
Why?

1018
01:01:40.530 --> 01:01:43.116
'Cause I don't know anybody

1019
01:01:43.200 --> 01:01:45.660
that can hear what she's been saying

1020
01:01:45.744 --> 01:01:47.245
and feel nothing.

1021
01:01:47.996 --> 01:01:49.748
I'm not saying it's right.

1022
01:01:51.249 --> 01:01:52.792
and I don't agree.

1023
01:01:53.501 --> 01:01:56.338
but I sure do hope
this works out for you. baby.

1024
01:01:58.131 --> 01:01:59.131
Thank you.

1025
01:02:07.974 --> 01:02:10.560
They always keep the air up
on high in here.

1026
01:02:12.270 --> 01:02:15.273
I have a jacket in my office.

1027
01:02:17.567 --> 01:02:18.777
And it's right there.

1028
01:02:20.654 --> 01:02:21.905
I can get it for you.

1029
01:02:34.876 --> 01:02:36.253
This is crazy.

1030
01:02:36.336 --> 01:02:39.214
- She has a bomb.
- Then hush.

1031
01:02:41.424 --> 01:02:43.009
Um…

1032
01:02:43.635 --> 01:02:44.635
Here it is.

1033
01:02:45.762 --> 01:02:46.763
Thank you.

1034
01:02:52.936 --> 01:02:57.274
Mm. Smells good. I like the perfume.

1035
01:02:57.774 --> 01:02:58.858
Is it expensive?

1036
01:03:00.819 --> 01:03:03.989
It was a gift from my husband.

1037
01:03:05.323 --> 01:03:07.325
Is he... Is he nice to you?

1038
01:03:07.909 --> 01:03:10.870
He's the best.

1039
01:03:13.331 --> 01:03:14.499
Good for you.

1040
01:03:16.334 --> 01:03:18.837
You gotta be so careful
who you have a baby with.

1041
01:03:20.839 --> 01:03:23.925
It seems like you had
a lot to get over today.

1042
01:03:24.718 --> 01:03:28.555
Black women always have
something to get over.

1043
01:03:33.310 --> 01:03:35.186
Is this your family?

1044
01:03:36.730 --> 01:03:38.231
Yes. it is.

1045
01:03:40.859 --> 01:03:43.570
Big brick house in the suburbs. huh?

1046
01:03:44.070 --> 01:03:45.405
It's not so big.

1047
01:03:45.488 --> 01:03:47.157
Oh. it's big to me.

1048
01:03:48.575 --> 01:03:50.243
Hmm. Hmm.

1049
01:03:50.869 --> 01:03:53.413
My apartment ain't
no bigger than this room.

1050
01:03:55.790 --> 01:03:57.500
I always dreamed of

1051
01:03:58.001 --> 01:04:00.837
having a place like that
for me and my baby.

1052
01:04:03.173 --> 01:04:06.426
How old... How old are your kids?

1053
01:04:08.887 --> 01:04:11.056
My oldest is Jennifer.

1054
01:04:11.139 --> 01:04:14.267
and she's 16.

1055
01:04:14.351 --> 01:04:16.269
- Hmm.
- And…

1056
01:04:18.521 --> 01:04:23.026
My youngest is Jasmine.

1057
01:04:23.818 --> 01:04:26.321
and she's seven.

1058
01:04:28.239 --> 01:04:31.451
Aria. That's my daughter.

1059
01:04:32.702 --> 01:04:36.414
She's got so many complications
I hope she grows out of.

1060
01:04:36.498 --> 01:04:38.124
especially the seizures.

1061
01:04:40.168 --> 01:04:42.295
I've seen you in here with her.

1062
01:04:43.922 --> 01:04:45.340
How attentive you are.

1063
01:04:48.051 --> 01:04:49.928
I notice those things.

1064
01:04:54.891 --> 01:04:56.184
For what it's worth.

1065
01:04:56.976 --> 01:05:00.021
I see so many single mothers come in here.

1066
01:05:01.773 --> 01:05:04.067
I swear if I didn't have my husband.

1067
01:05:04.818 --> 01:05:06.152
I don't know what I would do.

1068
01:05:06.236 --> 01:05:08.988
No. You figure it out.

1069
01:05:10.448 --> 01:05:14.953
Well. we need to figure this out

1070
01:05:16.371 --> 01:05:19.833
so you can get back to your daughter.

1071
01:05:21.668 --> 01:05:25.672
And I can get back to my family.

1072
01:05:27.215 --> 01:05:29.134
You will.

1073
01:05:30.176 --> 01:05:33.054
But they gonna put me in jail
for all of this.

1074
01:05:38.393 --> 01:05:41.563
Janiyah. I'm not gonna lie to you.

1075
01:05:43.440 --> 01:05:45.024
This is bad.

1076
01:05:45.108 --> 01:05:46.108
I know.

1077
01:05:48.069 --> 01:05:50.530
You will spend time in there.

1078
01:05:51.823 --> 01:05:53.533
but you will get out.

1079
01:05:54.159 --> 01:05:56.995
and your daughter will be waiting.

1080
01:05:59.539 --> 01:06:01.416
So what does that mean for her?

1081
01:06:02.167 --> 01:06:03.460
Foster care?

1082
01:06:06.004 --> 01:06:07.004
No.

1083
01:06:09.466 --> 01:06:12.969
Is there somebody in your family
that can help?

1084
01:06:14.012 --> 01:06:15.012
No.

1085
01:06:15.847 --> 01:06:18.766
I don't want her anywhere near
my sister and my mother. They are crazy.

1086
01:06:19.517 --> 01:06:20.560
It's okay.

1087
01:06:21.144 --> 01:06:24.397
It's okay because
we are all gonna walk out of here

1088
01:06:24.481 --> 01:06:27.609
as soon as they let that man go.

1089
01:06:27.692 --> 01:06:30.111
Soon as they get rid of that cop. Come on.

1090
01:06:39.245 --> 01:06:40.245
Shit!

1091
01:06:42.582 --> 01:06:46.711
- I knew it wouldn't be long.
- This can get ugly very quick.

1092
01:06:46.794 --> 01:06:49.339
- I need you to help to find that officer.
- I'm trying.

1093
01:06:59.057 --> 01:07:00.057
What is that?

1094
01:07:04.812 --> 01:07:06.564
- I don't know.
- Well. go see.

1095
01:07:18.910 --> 01:07:20.119
What are they saying?

1096
01:07:25.083 --> 01:07:27.043
They're saying. "Free Janiyah."

1097
01:07:32.840 --> 01:07:34.175
They're here for you.

1098
01:07:34.968 --> 01:07:35.969
It's on the news.

1099
01:07:38.429 --> 01:07:40.890
<i>Free Janiyah! Free Janiyah!</i>

1100
01:07:41.641 --> 01:07:47.689
<i>Free Janiyah! Free Janiyah!
Free Janiyah! Free Janiyah!</i>

1101
01:07:54.237 --> 01:08:00.910
Free Janiyah! Free Janiyah!
Free Janiyah! Free Janiyah! Free Janiyah…

1102
01:08:03.413 --> 01:08:07.083
Let's see if I can get in this crowd
and see what's going on.

1103
01:08:07.166 --> 01:08:09.210
Hi. ma'am. why are you here?

1104
01:08:09.294 --> 01:08:12.014
Because we're tired of all this
fucking shit! We go through too much.

1105
01:08:12.088 --> 01:08:15.842
We can't have the colorful language.
Oh. sir. what about you?

1106
01:08:15.925 --> 01:08:17.844
My name is Benny. I know her.

1107
01:08:17.927 --> 01:08:20.346
<i>She ain't lying.
She's been going through it.</i>

1108
01:08:20.847 --> 01:08:22.390
<i>I'm here for you. Janiyah.</i>

1109
01:08:25.226 --> 01:08:27.562
I'm homeless.
She ain't hardly have nothing.

1110
01:08:27.645 --> 01:08:29.689
<i>But she made sure I had something to eat.</i>

1111
01:08:30.440 --> 01:08:34.319
<i>But you do know
that she is wanted for murder.</i>

1112
01:08:35.111 --> 01:08:37.113
<i>But what did them motherfuckers do?</i>

1113
01:08:37.196 --> 01:08:38.281
<i>Shit. I get it.</i>

1114
01:08:38.364 --> 01:08:40.241
<i>All this shit'll make you snap.</i>

1115
01:08:40.325 --> 01:08:42.243
<i>Go live. Janiyah. Go live on your phone.</i>

1116
01:08:42.327 --> 01:08:45.455
<i>I want to apologize
to our viewers for the language.</i>

1117
01:08:45.538 --> 01:08:48.333
<i>but as you can see. this crowd is feeling</i>

1118
01:08:48.416 --> 01:08:51.919
very passionate
and emotional about this situation.

1119
01:08:52.003 --> 01:08:52.879
I have to tell you.

1120
01:08:52.962 --> 01:08:55.715
this crowd is in full support

1121
01:08:55.798 --> 01:08:57.884
of the alleged bank robber.

1122
01:08:57.967 --> 01:09:00.053
I've never seen anything like this.

1123
01:09:03.473 --> 01:09:05.808
All right. everybody out.
FBI's taking over.

1124
01:09:05.892 --> 01:09:08.102
- Shit.
- Come on. let's go.

1125
01:09:08.603 --> 01:09:10.938
Chief. you were in charge.
Now we're in charge.

1126
01:09:11.022 --> 01:09:12.190
Is that right?

1127
01:09:12.273 --> 01:09:14.609
That's right. Jim. grab that monitor.

1128
01:09:15.610 --> 01:09:17.570
- Susan. let me get you here.
- Yep.

1129
01:09:17.654 --> 01:09:19.989
Come on. Bryce.
You know we have this under control.

1130
01:09:20.073 --> 01:09:22.784
This has been going on for hours.
I would say that you don't.

1131
01:09:22.867 --> 01:09:25.286
Well. we made contact.
We're just working on getting her out.

1132
01:09:25.870 --> 01:09:26.746
Okay.

1133
01:09:26.829 --> 01:09:29.040
Well. that is
the whole objective. isn't it?

1134
01:09:29.123 --> 01:09:30.123
Yeah.

1135
01:09:30.541 --> 01:09:31.959
Seven hostages?

1136
01:09:32.043 --> 01:09:33.169
She released two.

1137
01:09:33.252 --> 01:09:34.379
And a bomb.

1138
01:09:34.462 --> 01:09:36.547
We're assuming. but. uh.

1139
01:09:36.631 --> 01:09:40.968
you know. I have a very strong feeling
that she's going to surrender peacefully.

1140
01:09:41.052 --> 01:09:42.052
A feeling?

1141
01:09:42.512 --> 01:09:48.101
Yeah. Our officer she bonded with.
Detective Raymond. right here.

1142
01:09:48.893 --> 01:09:49.727
This officer?

1143
01:09:49.811 --> 01:09:50.645
Yeah.

1144
01:09:50.728 --> 01:09:53.314
Okay. Listen. Chief.

1145
01:09:53.398 --> 01:09:55.358
You let this woman go live

1146
01:09:55.441 --> 01:09:57.485
and create a mob frenzy outside
of the bank.

1147
01:09:57.568 --> 01:09:59.362
I don't think you have this under control.

1148
01:09:59.445 --> 01:10:00.988
I strongly disagree.

1149
01:10:01.072 --> 01:10:02.573
She murdered her boss in cold blood.

1150
01:10:02.657 --> 01:10:06.744
She's got a bomb inside the bank.
and you have her bonding with an officer.

1151
01:10:06.828 --> 01:10:08.663
I don't think you have this under control.

1152
01:10:09.163 --> 01:10:11.958
So. as I said. we're taking over.

1153
01:10:12.959 --> 01:10:16.337
- Agent Bryce...
- Chief Wilson. you know what's next.

1154
01:10:16.838 --> 01:10:19.465
This is federal. so we're taking over.

1155
01:10:24.804 --> 01:10:26.556
We gotta find this damn officer.

1156
01:10:26.639 --> 01:10:28.099
All right.

1157
01:10:34.355 --> 01:10:36.190
I know you don't remember this.

1158
01:10:37.108 --> 01:10:40.403
but I was coming out of
the check cashing place across the street.

1159
01:10:40.486 --> 01:10:44.407
and you were trying to get me
to open up an account here.

1160
01:10:46.576 --> 01:10:49.412
You told me to stop
letting them take money from me.

1161
01:10:52.415 --> 01:10:54.792
I opened up an account because of you.

1162
01:11:00.798 --> 01:11:02.592
Why do you care so much?

1163
01:11:12.518 --> 01:11:15.396
I used to work at
the East Dale branch. and. uh.

1164
01:11:16.647 --> 01:11:19.108
all the women coming in with money.

1165
01:11:19.734 --> 01:11:23.029
they would get credit cards
and loans like it was nothing.

1166
01:11:23.905 --> 01:11:27.450
So I asked to be moved here.
so I could help us.

1167
01:11:29.410 --> 01:11:31.579
But there was so much red tape.

1168
01:11:32.079 --> 01:11:35.291
so much built into us not getting ahead.

1169
01:11:38.628 --> 01:11:40.838
I just wanted to make a difference.

1170
01:11:41.547 --> 01:11:43.382
You are making a difference.

1171
01:11:43.883 --> 01:11:46.469
Says the woman who is robbing the bank.

1172
01:11:47.970 --> 01:11:49.931
You ain't a nice person.

1173
01:11:50.556 --> 01:11:54.310
Oh. I'm sorry if I'm testy.
but we've been sitting here for hours.

1174
01:11:55.228 --> 01:11:57.188
And it's getting so hot.

1175
01:11:57.271 --> 01:11:59.440
Yes. Why is it so hot in here?

1176
01:12:06.030 --> 01:12:07.907
They turned off the AC.

1177
01:12:08.866 --> 01:12:12.662
They don't know me.
'cause I sleep in heat like this.

1178
01:12:13.830 --> 01:12:15.540
You don't have air conditioning?

1179
01:12:17.166 --> 01:12:18.166
No.

1180
01:12:19.377 --> 01:12:21.712
I was born in 1943.

1181
01:12:22.213 --> 01:12:24.507
We didn't even know anything
about an air conditioner

1182
01:12:24.590 --> 01:12:26.384
or a bathroom where I grew up.

1183
01:12:27.301 --> 01:12:30.680
Y'all just don't know how good you got it.

1184
01:12:30.763 --> 01:12:32.682
Even you.

1185
01:12:34.225 --> 01:12:35.393
'Cause. baby.

1186
01:12:35.476 --> 01:12:36.978
as bad as it is.

1187
01:12:37.061 --> 01:12:39.272
there's always somebody doing worse.

1188
01:12:40.147 --> 01:12:41.147
I know.

1189
01:12:41.649 --> 01:12:43.484
That's why I always try to be grateful.

1190
01:12:44.318 --> 01:12:46.320
Baby. walking out there

1191
01:12:46.404 --> 01:12:49.407
and giving up is being grateful.

1192
01:12:55.705 --> 01:12:57.456
I didn't mean to do this.

1193
01:12:59.125 --> 01:13:00.126
Okay?

1194
01:13:00.793 --> 01:13:02.670
Um. I…

1195
01:13:03.254 --> 01:13:04.380
I just. uh…

1196
01:13:06.299 --> 01:13:08.551
When I was at the hospital
with my daughter.

1197
01:13:09.343 --> 01:13:10.595
I just…

1198
01:13:12.555 --> 01:13:15.975
Something inside of me broke. and I just

1199
01:13:17.059 --> 01:13:20.271
feel like I've been floating
outside of myself ever since.

1200
01:13:23.900 --> 01:13:25.401
You know. that. um…

1201
01:13:26.235 --> 01:13:28.029
That hospital. they…

1202
01:13:29.614 --> 01:13:30.615
They don't care.

1203
01:13:32.658 --> 01:13:35.953
Um. my baby was a preemie.

1204
01:13:36.829 --> 01:13:38.789
so when my water broke.

1205
01:13:39.498 --> 01:13:42.543
they was telling me everything
that was wrong with her. and…

1206
01:13:44.879 --> 01:13:46.672
I just knew something wasn't right.

1207
01:13:47.798 --> 01:13:50.301
And the doctor kept telling me to sit up.

1208
01:13:50.968 --> 01:13:52.053
He said. "Sit up!"

1209
01:13:52.845 --> 01:13:54.013
And I knew that wasn't right.

1210
01:13:54.096 --> 01:13:58.225
and they was trying
to make me abort my baby.

1211
01:14:00.603 --> 01:14:02.355
I know it sounds crazy. but…

1212
01:14:04.357 --> 01:14:08.152
I'm telling the truth. and you know.
when you don't have insurance…

1213
01:14:10.905 --> 01:14:12.323
I believe you.

1214
01:14:13.199 --> 01:14:16.661
People don't know
how expensive it is to be poor.

1215
01:14:19.705 --> 01:14:21.916
I just don't have anybody.

1216
01:14:24.377 --> 01:14:27.213
Well. you got me.

1217
01:14:33.427 --> 01:14:36.514
Will you take my daughter for me
when they lock me up?

1218
01:14:38.891 --> 01:14:41.477
Like. foster care. just…

1219
01:14:41.560 --> 01:14:43.938
Keep her until I get out?

1220
01:14:45.773 --> 01:14:47.608
She won't be no problem either.

1221
01:14:47.692 --> 01:14:49.694
because she's a good girl.

1222
01:14:49.777 --> 01:14:52.029
She beat every odd so far.

1223
01:14:52.989 --> 01:14:54.865
She wasn't supposed to make it.

1224
01:14:57.994 --> 01:14:59.912
Please.

1225
01:14:59.996 --> 01:15:03.207
Because I don't have anybody else
to do it.

1226
01:15:07.336 --> 01:15:09.463
I will.

1227
01:15:10.965 --> 01:15:12.591
I will talk to my husband.

1228
01:15:13.300 --> 01:15:17.722
and I know he will say yes.

1229
01:15:19.265 --> 01:15:20.391
I will.

1230
01:15:20.975 --> 01:15:21.975
Thank you.

1231
01:15:25.855 --> 01:15:26.939
I'm sorry.

1232
01:15:27.565 --> 01:15:29.567
- I'm feeling bad.
- Oh.

1233
01:15:30.818 --> 01:15:31.861
Oh.

1234
01:15:32.695 --> 01:15:34.613
Can you get her some water?

1235
01:15:37.616 --> 01:15:40.369
Wait. Are you diabetic?

1236
01:15:41.078 --> 01:15:42.288
Yes.

1237
01:15:42.371 --> 01:15:43.414
Oh no. no.

1238
01:15:43.497 --> 01:15:46.000
Okay. we gotta let her out.
We gotta let her out.

1239
01:15:46.083 --> 01:15:47.668
Okay. Tessa.

1240
01:15:47.752 --> 01:15:49.628
- Okay. Miss Isabella.
- Go. Take her.

1241
01:15:49.712 --> 01:15:51.756
- Okay. come on. Miss Isabella.
- Be careful.

1242
01:15:51.839 --> 01:15:52.840
Come on.

1243
01:15:52.923 --> 01:15:54.633
I'm so sorry.

1244
01:15:54.717 --> 01:15:56.969
Okay. I got you.

1245
01:15:59.305 --> 01:16:02.475
You take care of yourself. girl. Okay?

1246
01:16:02.558 --> 01:16:04.268
Okay.

1247
01:16:04.351 --> 01:16:05.351
Okay.

1248
01:16:05.770 --> 01:16:07.271
Come on. Miss Isabella.

1249
01:16:07.354 --> 01:16:09.857
- Ooh Lord.
- Make sure she gets the help. okay?

1250
01:16:09.940 --> 01:16:11.192
Okay.

1251
01:16:18.908 --> 01:16:20.618
She needs a doctor!

1252
01:16:22.369 --> 01:16:24.455
She needs a doctor!

1253
01:16:24.538 --> 01:16:27.666
Hey. she's a customer.
Hold fire. Hold your fucking fire!

1254
01:16:27.750 --> 01:16:29.668
Be careful! She's a diabetic.

1255
01:16:29.752 --> 01:16:30.961
Take your hands off me!

1256
01:16:34.256 --> 01:16:36.425
Listen. I can't let you go in there.
I'm sorry.

1257
01:16:36.509 --> 01:16:39.845
She trusts me.
I'm not leaving my folks in there.

1258
01:16:39.929 --> 01:16:41.013
Ma'am.

1259
01:16:47.520 --> 01:16:49.939
One of your officers
let a hostage back in the building.

1260
01:16:50.022 --> 01:16:51.148
Get the fuck off me.

1261
01:16:52.108 --> 01:16:56.278
Free Janiyah! Free Janiyah! Free Janiyah!

1262
01:16:56.362 --> 01:16:59.365
Free Janiyah! Free Janiyah!

1263
01:16:59.949 --> 01:17:01.534
I hope she's gonna be okay.

1264
01:17:02.660 --> 01:17:03.660
They got her.

1265
01:17:04.620 --> 01:17:06.205
Okay.

1266
01:17:13.254 --> 01:17:15.005
Detective Raymond.

1267
01:17:15.089 --> 01:17:17.049
Yeah. she's a diabetic.

1268
01:17:17.133 --> 01:17:18.467
They need to check her levels.

1269
01:17:18.551 --> 01:17:20.344
Can you please let me know she's okay?

1270
01:17:20.427 --> 01:17:23.305
This is Agent Bryce with the FBI.
Is this Janiyah?

1271
01:17:23.806 --> 01:17:25.015
Uh…

1272
01:17:26.267 --> 01:17:27.977
Where... Where's Detective Raymond?

1273
01:17:28.561 --> 01:17:30.229
- I'm right...
- Hey!

1274
01:17:31.730 --> 01:17:34.984
Unh-unh. We're taking over
the investigation now.

1275
01:17:35.067 --> 01:17:36.527
How is everyone in there?

1276
01:17:36.610 --> 01:17:39.196
They're fine.
I need to speak to Detective Raymond.

1277
01:17:39.280 --> 01:17:41.115
Sorry. ma'am. You have to talk to me now.

1278
01:17:41.198 --> 01:17:42.741
Well. is that officer gone?

1279
01:17:43.784 --> 01:17:45.286
What officer is that. ma'am?

1280
01:17:45.369 --> 01:17:48.455
That's why I need to talk
to Detective Raymond.

1281
01:17:48.539 --> 01:17:49.540
because she knows.

1282
01:17:49.623 --> 01:17:51.625
Look. ma'am.
this has been going on long enough.

1283
01:17:51.709 --> 01:17:54.837
It's time for you to let the hostages go
and come out and surrender.

1284
01:17:54.920 --> 01:17:58.674
I'm not going nowhere
until I know that officer is gone!

1285
01:17:58.757 --> 01:18:00.634
I'm not going over this with you again!

1286
01:18:00.718 --> 01:18:01.927
Ma'am. when you rob a bank.

1287
01:18:02.011 --> 01:18:04.722
you don't get to pick
and choose what you wanna do. okay?

1288
01:18:04.805 --> 01:18:07.141
I'm not robbing the bank!

1289
01:18:07.224 --> 01:18:08.851
<i>This is a federal crime</i>.

1290
01:18:09.435 --> 01:18:12.855
It's been going on long enough.
We need you to come out of the bank.

1291
01:18:12.938 --> 01:18:15.983
I'm not coming out
until I know that officer's gone.

1292
01:18:16.483 --> 01:18:17.568
<i>Ma'am.</i>

1293
01:18:19.445 --> 01:18:22.531
He won't let me talk to Detective Raymond.

1294
01:18:22.615 --> 01:18:24.533
I need to talk to Detective Raymond!

1295
01:18:24.617 --> 01:18:28.746
Sir... Sir. please...
Please get Detective Raymond.

1296
01:18:28.829 --> 01:18:30.998
She only talks to me now. Who is this?

1297
01:18:31.081 --> 01:18:33.792
I'm Nicole. the branch manager.

1298
01:18:33.876 --> 01:18:35.794
Nicole. she needs to talk to me.

1299
01:18:35.878 --> 01:18:38.756
Please. sir. get Detective Raymond.

1300
01:18:41.425 --> 01:18:44.386
- Ugh! This thing is driving me crazy!
- She's picked up the backpack!

1301
01:18:44.470 --> 01:18:47.014
- Janiyah. you don't have to do this.
- What?

1302
01:18:47.097 --> 01:18:49.516
Janiyah. please. Janiyah. please.

1303
01:18:49.600 --> 01:18:51.227
What's she doing now. ma'am?

1304
01:18:51.310 --> 01:18:53.437
- We can all walk out of here together.
- Please!

1305
01:18:53.520 --> 01:18:55.898
- This is driving me crazy!
- Janiyah. we can do this!

1306
01:18:55.981 --> 01:18:57.691
- Janiyah. please don't...
- So loud!

1307
01:18:57.775 --> 01:19:00.319
Oh my... Just hang up the phone!

1308
01:19:00.402 --> 01:19:01.528
Don't. please!

1309
01:19:03.197 --> 01:19:05.074
Nicole! Nicole!

1310
01:19:06.158 --> 01:19:07.826
- Please!
- Please don't do this!

1311
01:19:07.910 --> 01:19:10.120
- Please!
- Don't! Don't!

1312
01:19:10.204 --> 01:19:11.538
Come on!

1313
01:19:15.709 --> 01:19:17.670
Please.

1314
01:19:17.753 --> 01:19:18.753
Please.

1315
01:19:21.298 --> 01:19:22.508
My daughter made this.

1316
01:19:24.093 --> 01:19:25.552
Her science fair project.

1317
01:19:26.303 --> 01:19:27.846
It drives me crazy.

1318
01:19:29.265 --> 01:19:31.850
It's… It's not a bomb?

1319
01:19:34.645 --> 01:19:35.562
No.

1320
01:19:35.646 --> 01:19:37.273
It's not a bomb. It's…

1321
01:19:40.609 --> 01:19:42.653
They think this is a bomb?

1322
01:19:44.905 --> 01:19:45.905
All this time?

1323
01:19:48.617 --> 01:19:51.245
You... It's not a...

1324
01:19:51.328 --> 01:19:53.163
Can you call
and tell them it's not a bomb?

1325
01:19:53.247 --> 01:19:56.000
It's for my daughter's
science fair project.

1326
01:19:56.083 --> 01:19:58.919
You gotta call them
and tell them it's not a bomb.

1327
01:19:59.003 --> 01:20:01.880
If we explain that. then…
then they'll know.

1328
01:20:01.964 --> 01:20:03.424
I need to go to the bathroom.

1329
01:20:03.507 --> 01:20:05.509
Go! Go! Tell them!

1330
01:20:05.592 --> 01:20:07.469
Tell them it's not a bomb!

1331
01:20:26.572 --> 01:20:28.782
We got a message.

1332
01:20:33.662 --> 01:20:35.956
"Bomb is not real. One gun."

1333
01:20:36.540 --> 01:20:39.001
- Call them and tell them.
- Okay. Okay.

1334
01:20:39.084 --> 01:20:40.252
Call Detective Raymond

1335
01:20:40.336 --> 01:20:43.422
and tell them it's...
It's been a big mistake.

1336
01:20:45.215 --> 01:20:47.843
Come on. you have to tell them
this is a science fair project.

1337
01:20:48.510 --> 01:20:49.510
What?

1338
01:20:51.764 --> 01:20:53.891
I don't think we should do that.

1339
01:20:53.974 --> 01:20:54.974
Why?

1340
01:20:58.354 --> 01:21:01.815
They have policies regarding explosives.

1341
01:21:02.900 --> 01:21:05.903
- But...
- That may be the only thing

1342
01:21:05.986 --> 01:21:08.405
that is keeping them from coming in

1343
01:21:08.489 --> 01:21:10.366
and storming the bank.

1344
01:21:11.825 --> 01:21:13.702
I don't want you to get hurt.

1345
01:21:15.371 --> 01:21:21.377
So. let's tell them
that we're going to come out.

1346
01:21:23.212 --> 01:21:25.339
and you're gonna leave the backpack.

1347
01:21:27.424 --> 01:21:29.176
You think that's for the best?

1348
01:21:30.135 --> 01:21:31.303
I do.

1349
01:21:36.141 --> 01:21:38.143
But that officer has to be gone.

1350
01:21:41.063 --> 01:21:42.272
Okay.

1351
01:21:42.856 --> 01:21:44.024
You promise me.

1352
01:21:47.111 --> 01:21:48.111
Promise.

1353
01:21:50.364 --> 01:21:51.490
Detective Raymond.

1354
01:21:51.573 --> 01:21:52.573
Yeah.

1355
01:21:53.617 --> 01:21:54.617
Tell her.

1356
01:21:55.702 --> 01:21:57.162
I wrote her the tickets today.

1357
01:21:58.038 --> 01:22:00.624
Expired registration and so on. all legit.

1358
01:22:01.125 --> 01:22:02.918
- Did you tow her car?
- Yes.

1359
01:22:03.001 --> 01:22:05.082
- Did you run her off the road?
- No. I didn't do that.

1360
01:22:05.129 --> 01:22:08.298
Okay. She said there was
another officer there. Who was it?

1361
01:22:09.925 --> 01:22:13.053
I don't have time for your bullshit.
Officer Sam. Just tell me.

1362
01:22:14.847 --> 01:22:17.182
I don't really know.
She said it was a cop.

1363
01:22:17.266 --> 01:22:19.393
You fucking lying to me.
You fucking lying to me?

1364
01:22:19.476 --> 01:22:21.186
Tell me the fucking truth!

1365
01:22:23.105 --> 01:22:25.190
- Who was it?
- It was Officer Oliver.

1366
01:22:25.274 --> 01:22:27.025
Did he hit her car?

1367
01:22:27.109 --> 01:22:28.026
I didn't see him.

1368
01:22:28.110 --> 01:22:30.237
Was there any damage to the car?

1369
01:22:31.196 --> 01:22:32.906
- Yes. It looked like he pitted her.
- Bet.

1370
01:22:40.080 --> 01:22:43.333
Raymond. Raymond. come on.
Don't... Don't do this.

1371
01:22:48.505 --> 01:22:51.049
Hey. hey. hey! What in the hell
is going on. Detective Raymond?

1372
01:22:51.133 --> 01:22:52.676
He know what the fuck is going on!

1373
01:22:52.759 --> 01:22:54.970
Tell him what you did.
Tell him what the fuck you did!

1374
01:22:55.053 --> 01:22:56.053
I didn't do shit.

1375
01:22:56.096 --> 01:22:57.723
What in the hell is going on?

1376
01:22:57.806 --> 01:22:58.932
What's going on?

1377
01:22:59.016 --> 01:23:00.601
He gave her a fucking ticket.

1378
01:23:00.684 --> 01:23:03.103
He ran her off the road.
He caused all this shit!

1379
01:23:05.731 --> 01:23:07.691
I got the proof. Chief. I got it.

1380
01:23:09.860 --> 01:23:10.860
He did it.

1381
01:23:11.737 --> 01:23:13.947
You… with me right now.

1382
01:23:14.031 --> 01:23:15.031
Let's go.

1383
01:23:17.034 --> 01:23:19.620
You're done. motherfucker! You're done!

1384
01:23:23.749 --> 01:23:26.752
Agent Bryce. we know who the officer is.

1385
01:23:27.461 --> 01:23:30.172
- I said no more talking.
- The damn phones are ringing.

1386
01:23:30.255 --> 01:23:32.257
- Answer the phone.
- I said no more talking.

1387
01:23:33.800 --> 01:23:35.302
Answer the damn phone!

1388
01:23:35.886 --> 01:23:37.304
Fuck it and fuck you!

1389
01:23:37.387 --> 01:23:38.430
God damn it!

1390
01:23:39.056 --> 01:23:40.599
This is Detective Raymond.

1391
01:23:42.226 --> 01:23:43.560
It's Detective Raymond.

1392
01:23:44.686 --> 01:23:46.563
Oh.

1393
01:23:46.647 --> 01:23:47.647
Hello?

1394
01:23:48.357 --> 01:23:49.942
- Detective Raymond.
<i>- Yes.</i>

1395
01:23:50.025 --> 01:23:51.401
Who was that asshole?

1396
01:23:52.694 --> 01:23:53.862
You have me now.

1397
01:23:55.364 --> 01:23:58.325
I just wanted to let you know
that we found the officer.

1398
01:24:00.035 --> 01:24:00.869
You did?

1399
01:24:00.953 --> 01:24:03.372
<i>Yes. it took us a minute
because he's in the county over.</i>

1400
01:24:03.455 --> 01:24:06.500
<i>The officer that gave you the ticket
told us that it was him.</i>

1401
01:24:06.583 --> 01:24:09.086
And judging by the damage of your car.
he hit you.

1402
01:24:09.753 --> 01:24:11.004
Promise.

1403
01:24:11.672 --> 01:24:12.714
I promise.

1404
01:24:14.091 --> 01:24:16.134
Okay. I wanna see a picture then.

1405
01:24:16.218 --> 01:24:17.386
A picture?

1406
01:24:18.053 --> 01:24:19.680
I want you to prove to me

1407
01:24:19.763 --> 01:24:22.391
that you know who it is.
I wanna see a picture.

1408
01:24:22.891 --> 01:24:25.060
I can show you that.
Janiyah. when you come out. okay?

1409
01:24:25.143 --> 01:24:27.271
No. No.

1410
01:24:29.773 --> 01:24:30.816
Text it to me.

1411
01:24:31.316 --> 01:24:33.068
Janiyah. your phone is not on.

1412
01:24:33.151 --> 01:24:36.071
<i>The ones you are using there
in the bank are only for inner calls.</i>

1413
01:24:41.368 --> 01:24:43.328
Okay. well. then turn my phone back on.

1414
01:24:43.412 --> 01:24:45.205
You can do it. You have the power.

1415
01:24:45.289 --> 01:24:48.458
The FBI can turn my phone back on
and then text me the picture.

1416
01:24:49.918 --> 01:24:50.918
And you'll come out?

1417
01:24:50.961 --> 01:24:53.839
Yes. I'll come out. Text me the picture.

1418
01:24:53.922 --> 01:24:55.841
Okay. Now let me get your phone turned on.

1419
01:24:55.924 --> 01:24:58.635
No. not a chance.
She has to give me the hostages.

1420
01:25:01.972 --> 01:25:04.683
<i>Janiyah. the FBI can turn your phone on.</i>

1421
01:25:04.766 --> 01:25:06.810
But we're gonna need
something in exchange. okay?

1422
01:25:07.352 --> 01:25:08.270
<i>Okay.</i>

1423
01:25:08.353 --> 01:25:10.897
Well. send me the picture.
and I'll let everybody go.

1424
01:25:11.398 --> 01:25:13.775
Come on. This is worth a chance.

1425
01:25:17.237 --> 01:25:18.697
Are you gonna send it?

1426
01:25:20.407 --> 01:25:22.743
Yes. we're getting your phone turned on.

1427
01:25:23.493 --> 01:25:24.493
Okay.

1428
01:25:26.538 --> 01:25:29.541
But when you send me the picture.
then everybody can go.

1429
01:25:31.084 --> 01:25:33.754
And then you tell them what he did to me.

1430
01:25:34.296 --> 01:25:36.423
You show everybody what he did to me.

1431
01:25:36.506 --> 01:25:38.842
And 'cause I wasn't lying!

1432
01:25:38.925 --> 01:25:42.012
You let everybody know
I was telling the truth. okay?

1433
01:25:42.512 --> 01:25:45.390
Yes. Yes. we will. Yes.

1434
01:25:45.932 --> 01:25:50.187
And I know that female officer
had a body cam. She saw it.

1435
01:25:50.270 --> 01:25:54.066
She made him go back to his car
because she heard him threaten me.

1436
01:25:54.149 --> 01:25:56.485
Okay. and then you will come out?

1437
01:25:56.568 --> 01:25:58.153
Yes. I'll come out.

1438
01:25:58.236 --> 01:26:00.739
And you're gonna leave the gun
in the backpack. right?

1439
01:26:00.822 --> 01:26:01.823
Yes.

1440
01:26:03.909 --> 01:26:06.453
So when you walk out.
hold your hands up high.

1441
01:26:07.079 --> 01:26:09.665
And back up slowly.
directly toward the police.

1442
01:26:12.834 --> 01:26:14.211
You gonna be there?

1443
01:26:15.420 --> 01:26:18.632
Yes. it will be me. Just follow my voice.

1444
01:26:20.592 --> 01:26:21.592
Okay.

1445
01:26:24.429 --> 01:26:25.555
<i>I'll call you back.</i>

1446
01:26:27.849 --> 01:26:29.184
Just send the picture.

1447
01:26:30.644 --> 01:26:32.688
I'll get the photo to you
in a second. all right?

1448
01:26:43.115 --> 01:26:45.242
They found him.

1449
01:26:46.910 --> 01:26:48.161
They found him.

1450
01:26:48.245 --> 01:26:49.746
I told you.

1451
01:26:49.830 --> 01:26:51.665
I wasn't lying. They found him.

1452
01:26:56.837 --> 01:26:58.505
I told you I wasn't lying.

1453
01:27:05.512 --> 01:27:07.013
Shut down all the lights.

1454
01:27:07.097 --> 01:27:08.807
- Wait. what?
- We're going in.

1455
01:27:08.890 --> 01:27:11.226
She's literally coming out!
Why would we be going in?

1456
01:27:11.309 --> 01:27:13.937
This has been going on
for 12 hours. all right?

1457
01:27:14.020 --> 01:27:15.021
Do you see those people?

1458
01:27:15.105 --> 01:27:16.440
No. do you see this?

1459
01:27:16.523 --> 01:27:19.443
They will fucking riot.
We can end this peacefully.

1460
01:27:20.444 --> 01:27:21.486
You had your time.

1461
01:27:21.570 --> 01:27:23.405
Turn the damn phones on.

1462
01:27:28.618 --> 01:27:30.120
Is everyone in place?

1463
01:27:36.543 --> 01:27:38.545
Fucking kidding me.

1464
01:27:43.467 --> 01:27:46.470
Free Janiyah…

1465
01:27:55.061 --> 01:27:57.522
Oh! Raymond. what are you doing?

1466
01:27:57.606 --> 01:27:59.357
Detective Raymond. what are you doing?

1467
01:28:06.239 --> 01:28:07.824
What the hell is she doing?

1468
01:28:08.658 --> 01:28:10.202
Detective Raymond!

1469
01:28:21.296 --> 01:28:22.464
Who is that banging?

1470
01:28:22.547 --> 01:28:24.466
Janiyah!

1471
01:28:24.549 --> 01:28:26.259
It's Detective Raymond.

1472
01:28:26.343 --> 01:28:28.512
Ooh.

1473
01:28:31.640 --> 01:28:34.726
Janiyah. it's Detective Raymond.
I've been speaking with you.

1474
01:28:36.478 --> 01:28:37.687
What does she want?

1475
01:28:38.188 --> 01:28:41.066
They will not turn your phone back on.
Janiyah. I'm sorry.

1476
01:28:41.149 --> 01:28:44.402
But I have the proof here in my phone.
I can show you the photos right here.

1477
01:28:44.903 --> 01:28:47.072
Okay. open it. Get the phone.

1478
01:28:47.656 --> 01:28:49.950
He's gone. I promise.

1479
01:28:51.076 --> 01:28:52.077
Okay.

1480
01:28:52.994 --> 01:28:55.705
I'll take it to her.

1481
01:29:01.461 --> 01:29:03.129
That's him! That's him!

1482
01:29:03.213 --> 01:29:05.173
I told you I wasn't lying.

1483
01:29:06.842 --> 01:29:07.968
I know you weren't.

1484
01:29:09.302 --> 01:29:10.679
Okay. tell her that's him.

1485
01:29:18.311 --> 01:29:19.396
She says it's him.

1486
01:29:20.272 --> 01:29:21.272
He's gone.

1487
01:29:24.860 --> 01:29:25.861
Y'all can go.

1488
01:29:27.696 --> 01:29:29.573
Come on. Tessa. Rayah.

1489
01:29:37.289 --> 01:29:38.289
Wait.

1490
01:29:38.748 --> 01:29:39.791
What are you doing?

1491
01:29:40.292 --> 01:29:41.292
No. go on.

1492
01:29:41.334 --> 01:29:42.627
- What are you doing?
- Go.

1493
01:29:48.550 --> 01:29:50.093
I'm gonna walk with her.

1494
01:29:51.094 --> 01:29:52.094
Okay.

1495
01:30:01.771 --> 01:30:03.523
No. You go.

1496
01:30:04.190 --> 01:30:05.567
You can go.

1497
01:30:05.650 --> 01:30:06.650
No.

1498
01:30:07.819 --> 01:30:09.529
We're gonna do this together.

1499
01:30:17.287 --> 01:30:19.915
I never had anybody stand by me

1500
01:30:21.458 --> 01:30:22.500
before.

1501
01:30:25.378 --> 01:30:26.755
I'm sorry.

1502
01:30:29.007 --> 01:30:30.759
For all of this.

1503
01:30:32.260 --> 01:30:33.260
You got me.

1504
01:30:36.890 --> 01:30:39.643
Will you come visit me
when they lock me up?

1505
01:30:41.728 --> 01:30:44.356
Yes. I promise you.

1506
01:30:46.149 --> 01:30:49.903
I will come visit you with Aria.

1507
01:30:51.613 --> 01:30:53.114
And I will tell her

1508
01:30:53.823 --> 01:30:56.701
what a brave mother you are.

1509
01:30:58.370 --> 01:30:59.829
And please.

1510
01:30:59.913 --> 01:31:04.000
make sure my baby gets her $40 for lunch.

1511
01:31:05.919 --> 01:31:06.919
I will.

1512
01:31:11.466 --> 01:31:12.926
Make it happen.

1513
01:31:19.057 --> 01:31:21.267
My phone is on.

1514
01:31:25.230 --> 01:31:26.439
It's my mother.

1515
01:31:27.732 --> 01:31:28.566
Hello?

1516
01:31:28.650 --> 01:31:31.528
